Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the First Baptist Church in Dallas, Texas, celebrating freedom and emphasizing the importance of faith. He expressed gratitude for the support of Pastor Robert Jeffress and President Donald Trump. Pence spoke about the various ways in which the Trump administration has worked to protect and celebrate freedom, including strengthening the economy, rebuilding the military, standing with allies like Israel, and defending religious liberty. He also addressed recent events of civil unrest, condemning the violence and vandalism while acknowledging the need for justice in cases like George Floyd's. Pence emphasized the importance of prayer and faith in overcoming challenges and called on Americans to hold fast to their faith and celebrate freedom every day.